Click on a saint to compare their place of birth and place of death. Consider the difference in distance traveled between male saints and female saints. To see a statistical breakdown of birth and death regions, click the arrow on the right. 

Each monastery on this map was founded in or around the twelfth century. All but one were founded explicitly by members of the nobility. Notice how they are all clustered around Edinburgh. Hover your mouse over a monastery to see biographical details. Click each monastery to see a Google Street View of the location as it stands today. 

Welcome to the visualization page for "Mission, Myth, and Monasticism: Religious Archetypes and Cultural Transmission between Gaelic Ireland and Scotland, 1200-1500." This project uses Digital Humanities techniques to examine the spatiality of cultural exchange between Scotland and Gaelic Ireland, comparing early medieval conversion efforts with monastic correspondence in the 13th century until the Reformation.  